  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This multicenter open labeled phase 2 trial examines the efficacy of a combination of
      Gemcitabine 1000 mg/m2 (30 min), Cisplatin 30 mg/m2 (90 min), Folinic Acid 200 mg/m2 (30 min)
      and 5-FU 750 mg/m2 (24h CI) all given day 1,8 q D22 in patients with inoperable esophageal
      cancer. The combination was considered to be suitable for further evaluation with a freedom
      of progression rate (PR+CR+SD) of more than 60% and not be be of further interest with a rate
      of less than 40%. Given an alpha error of 5% and an beta error of 10% at least 66 evaluable
      patients were needed based on a 2-Stage Simon design with a first evaluation after 25
      evaluable patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
